fr.reflexe.viewshell.api.http

Interface IFormPart


  • public interface IFormPart
    Represents an item in a multipart form, such as fields and file uploads.
    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    REFLEXE Technologies

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      static String ATTACHMENT
      Content-Disposition header value.
      static String FORM_URLENCODED
      Common Content-Type value for forms without uploads.
      static String MULTIPART_FORM_DATA
      Normal Content-Type value for multipart HTML forms.
      static String MULTIPART_FORM_MIXED
      Normal Content-Type value for multipart web services.

      • getString

        String getString()
        Gets the value of the form field, or the contents of the field decoded using a default charset.

        The charset is determined if possible from the content type provided in the request with this item (if provided). If undefined, then the request charset is used to determine the encoding (if defined). Failing that, the implicit default is ISO-8859-1 as per IETF RFC 3875.

        Note: line breaks are converted to Unix format ("\n").

        Returns:
        the item as a string.
        Since:
        1.0

      • getString

        String getString(Charset encoding)
        Gets the value of the form field, or the contents of the field decoded using a specified charset.

        Note: line breaks are converted to Unix format ("\n").

        Parameters:
        encoding - the non-null charset used for decoding.
        Returns:
        the item as a string.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the encoding is not specified.
        Since:
        1.0
